text: In mathematics, a Dold manifold is one of the manifolds P(m,n) = (Sm×CPn)/τ (where τ acts as −1 on the sphere Sm and a complex conjugation on complex projective space CPn) constructed by that he used to give explicit generators for Thom's unoriented cobordism ring. ==References== * Category:Algebraic topology Category:Manifolds
title: Dold manifold
